@Node Description "Description"

  Description
  ===========

    This is a bulletin viewer, it is used to let the user choose a bulletin
    (i.e. text or screen file contining information) to display.

    Bulletins are stored in the "Screens/Bulletins" directory of each
    conference and node, as well as "HBBS:Screens/Bulletins".

    The door prompts the user for a bulletin name, this is then
    added onto the end of the string "Bulletin_" and then that screen
    is searched for in exactly the same way as a special screen is searched
    for.  (i.e. Access Levels, LanguageName/Ext and _DEF.TXT apply)

@EndNode

@Node Installation "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

    The doors is stored as HBBS:Doors/User/BulletinViewer/BulletinViewer.HBBS

    This is included and enabled with a fresh installation of HydraBBS
    since V1.01.  Users of prior version should do this:

    Add the following lines to the appropriate "commands" file:

    B_Type_1=HBBS
    B_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/User/BulletinViewer/BulletinViewer.HBBS {N} {O}

    See HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/Commands/All_Levels for an example

@EndNode

@Node SystemOptions "SystemOptions"

  System Options
  ==============

    None

@EndNode

@Node CmdLineOptions "CmdLineOptions"

  Command Line Options
  ====================

    <bulletin name> - If specified the bulletin will be displayed,
                      followed by a pause prompt.  The menu will
                      not be shown.

    If there are no command line options a menu will be displayed.
    which will let the user pick a bulletin to display.

@EndNode

@Node ScreensDisplayed "Screens Displayed"

  Screens Displayed
  =================

    Bulletins_TOP - Displayed before...
    Bulletins_LIST - List of bulletins the user can display
    Bulletins_BOT - Displayed after the above two screens

@EndNode

